<p>Tuesday 12/6/16<br/>Divisional sports which were to have been held today, have been postponed till tomorrow, on account of memorial service [indecipherable] Lord Kitchener.  Service held at 6 pm; very impressive.  Tents again struck &amp; this time we are quartered in a marquee, previously used as a hospital.  Piquet from 7 pm</p>
<p>Wednesday 14/6/16<br/>Twelve months to-day since I enlisted.  <br/>Divisional sports day; on piquet, but obtained permission to attend.<br/>Our unit again took first prize for best turned out limber, against allcomers of the Division.  Relieved from piquet 7 pm.</p>
<p>Thursday 15/6/16<br/>Spent the morning in the lake swimming.  Detailed for duty at railway siding 5 pm where I remained till 9 pm</p>
